Please edit this page to add your recommended R packages for all computers in biology:

1. ggplot2
1. dplyr
1. bbmle
1. chron
1. deSolve
1. maps
1. markdown
1. rmarkdown
1. shiny
1. tidyr
1. abind: combine multidimensional arrays
1. vegan: biodiversity analysis
1. devtools: developer tools
1. lubridate: working with dates

* In the computer labs, it may be better to install tidyverse instead of the individual packages from the tidyverse universe (e.g. ggplot2, dplyr, shiny).
